# Aggressive "minimal" list for a headless phone chroot. One package per line.
# Run: chroot-minimize.sh --profile minimal   (dry-run)
# Then edit: comment out anything you still need (X11 apps, NetHunter GUI, etc.)
# Do NOT remove kali metapackages you rely on without checking apt output first.
#
# === Already in packages-headless-remove.list; repeated so --profile minimal is self-contained ===
exim4-daemon-light
exim4-base
exim4-config
cups
cups-bsd
cups-daemon
cups-browsed
cups-client
cups-core-drivers
cups-filters
cups-ipp-utils
cups-ppdc
cups-server-common
cups-filters-core-drivers
ippusbxd
hplip
hplip-data
#
# === Mail (optional) — keep bsd-mailx if some tool needs /usr/bin/mail ===
# bsd-mailx
# mailutils
postfix
# sendmail
#
# === Network discovery on LAN (rarely needed in chroot) ===
avahi-daemon
avahi-utils
libnss-mdns
# (If something breaks: reinstall avahi-daemon or use minimal nsswitch.)
#
# === Color management / scanning (no scanner on device) ===
colord
sane
sane-utils
simple-scan
# xsane
#
# === Power desktop bits (chroot) ===
upower
power-profiles-daemon
#
# === Bluetooth / GUI pairing (headless) ===
blueman
bluez-cups
# bluez (WARNING: can break command-line BT if you use it; leave commented unless you know.)
# bluez-obexd
#
# === GUI network tools (if installed) — keep if you use NetHunter app ===
# network-manager-gnome
# nm-connection-editor
# modemmanager
#
# === Snap / flatpak (if present) ===
# snapd
# flatpak
# plasma-discover
# gnome-software
# packagekit
# packagekit-tools
#
# === Display managers & X stack (DANGER: Kali/NetHunter may need for VNC/keX) ===
# Uncomment only if you are 100% CLI-only in chroot.
# lightdm
# gdm3
# sddm
# slim
# xserver-xorg
# xserver-xorg-core
# xserver-xorg-input-all
# xorg
# x11-xserver-utils
# x11-common
# xinit
# x11-apps
# x11-utils
# x11-session-utils
#
# === Browsers (huge) — only if you will never browse from chroot ===
# firefox-esr
# chromium
# chromium-common
# thunderbird
#
# === Office / heavy desktop (if present) ===
# libreoffice-core
# libreoffice-common
# gimp
# inkscape
#
# === Wireshark UI — keep tshark, drop GUI if you use CLI only ===
# wireshark
# wireshark-qt
# wireshark-common
#
# === TeX / big dev stacks (if you did not ask for them) ===
# texlive-*
# (pattern not supported: add explicit texlive package names from: dpkg -l | grep texlive)
#
# === Games / emulators (if any) ===
# steam*
# (patterns unsupported — add names from dpkg -l)
#
# === Kali "surface" (optional) — can affect look but often safe ===
# kali-themes
# kali-theme-core
# kali-undercover
#
# === Extra locales (reclaim: use locale / localepurge manually if installed) ===
# localepurge
#
# === Virtualization (pointless in phone chroot) — comment if not present ===
# virtualbox-*
# qemu-system-x86
# libvirt0
# virt-manager
#
# Add more names from: chroot-audit.sh "largest installed packages"
